(35730, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you. Her wounds have closed.', 21463), -- 35730
(35025, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, friend. I am in your debt.$b$bThis arrogant Iron Horde has made a dangerous enemy today.', 21463), -- 35025
(35248, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I like killing things. And bones.', 21463), -- 35248
(35035, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Watch them burn!', 21463), -- 35035
(35880, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can see the future of my enemies in the bones. They''re gonna die!', 21463), -- 35880
(35151, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A fine choice. It will need more work before such a structure could be built in your garrison, but this is a start.', 21463), -- 35151
(36460, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perhaps this little creature will earn her keep after all.', 21463), -- 36460
(36434, 113, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ahh, there y''are!$b$bPenny Clobberbottom reportin'' for duty, commander.', 21463), -- 36434
(33593, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That didn''t seem to do much, commander, except to give away our position to every creature in Gorgrond.$b$bWait, did you hear something?', 21463), -- 33593
(33548, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These are more than fancy facewear. With a mask and some proper incentive, we can make anyone a Laughing Skull.', 21463), -- 33548
(33563, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These puppets of the magnaron will pay for the skulls they claimed today.$b$bFor now, I shall wear this eye across my waist so this fool you have slain may watch as I slowly slaughter his brethren until my dying breath.', 21463), -- 33563
(33544, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ripfist''s dying wish has been satisfied. Goren corpses litter the ground, and these corpses have not gone unnoticed by the nearby goren.', 21463), -- 33544
(33543, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ha! Curious. What are you?', 21463), -- 33543
(34867, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Gorgrond is no place for armies, commander. We are now stepping into the domain of legends.', 21463), -- 34867
(34075, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n.$b$bI wish we could bring him back just to kill him again but I guess this will suffice.$b$bI hope the spirit of my little one will now know peace.', 21463), -- 34075
(34102, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work,$n!$b$bSeeing Frostwolf banners standing proudly over our crushed foes fills me with pride!$b$bLet them forever fear the wrath of the Frostwolves!', 21463), -- 34102
(34073, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good job $n, I was able to use the commotion from your work to sneak into the camp.$b$bNow we have only one thing left to do.', 21463), -- 34073
(34070, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done $n! The removal of the Sky Riders takes the heat off us for a bit. Keep your weapon in hand though, we''re not done with them yet.', 21463), -- 34070
(34072, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ugh, those smell awful! No, I don''t need to see them. I''ll take you at your word that you have them all.$b$bLet''s get a move on before another Thunderlord patrol stumbles upon me.', 21463), -- 34072
(34069, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hrm, yes these spears look pretty good.$b$bNot bad! I know just what to use these for!', 21463), -- 34069
(34067, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Rope? Do you expect me to tie a noose and ask the Thunderlords to go hang themselves?$b$bWait... that gives me an idea. Yea, I think I can make this work with the right materials.$b$bGood Job.', 21463), -- 34067
(34066, 66, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done well, $c.$b$bNow before we can continue our assault we need to look for any supplies in the area that could help our fight.', 21463), -- 34066
(37563, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent choice. I will be sad to see them leave, but I know they will help strengthen our combined packs in the coming conflicts.$b$bI will see that they make their way to your garrison as soon as they have said farewell to their loved ones.$b$bThey should be ready the next time you need to send followers on a mission.', 21463), -- 37563
(34124, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This was a costly victory, and a very painful lesson. We chose to refuse the Iron Horde and live as we always have, but I see now they will never respect such neutrality.$b$bI am not about to wait for the Iron Horde to marshal their forces. We will fight with you, and bring the Iron Horde to its knees.$b$bCommander, the Frostwolves stand ready!', 21463), -- 34124
(34123, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am glad to see you. Our clan has faced many challenges, but the sheer size of the army coming toward us is beyond anything we have attempted to face.$b$bWe need your experience.', 21463), -- 34123
(34731, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My sista have other duties, but I have leave of ol'' Vol''jin to extend my services to you.$b$bYa proved your worth, and did a task that needed doing.$b$bI be followin'' ya, boss-mon, if ya be willing.', 21463), -- 34731
(34348, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now dat be a mighty fine haul. We gonna be keepin'' all the folks at the garrison warm.$b$bIt seemed like a simple task but ya tackled it like a boss-mon. If ya need a shadow hunter in your ranks, I be willin'' to serve.', 21463), -- 34348
(34344, 1, 11, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'Dem centipedes creep you out boss-mon? Touchin'' ya with their teeny tiny legs? I ain''t thought of a thing that makes me skin crawl more, except maybe mah sister''s voice. Hee hee.', 21463), -- 34344
(34345, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Haha! Ya brought ''em! I hope ya not offended I asked such a lowly task of ya. We needed the leaves, and I needed to settle a bet.', 21463), -- 34345
(34346, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, now these be some fine trap making props. Ya know how to make a shadow huntah proud.', 21463), -- 34346
(35341, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have proven yourself more powerful than my previous leaders. My service is yours.', 21463), -- 35341
(32981, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Strag was the puppet of the Iron Wolf. She would do nothing unless ordered to by him.$b$bThis made us weak, changing us from a force to be feared to a target.$b$bIf this is what the Thunderlord have become then I will have no part of them.', 21463), -- 32981
(33462, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With a quick tap of a hammer and a snip of the rings, the Thunderlord Grapple is as good as new.', 21463), -- 33462
(34736, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Eh dere, boss-mon! Watch ya step. Da ground be cracklin'' and breakin'' everywhere.', 21463), -- 34736
(34960, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now this is some handy stuff. This weather has been cutting through our supplies of rope so quick we need something we can use to provide an alternative. Looks like you scored the jackpot.', 21463), -- 34960
(33010, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for protecting my family, $p.', 21463), -- 33010
(37291, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well fought, commander. Now to strike back before the Thunderlord can recover.', 21463), -- 37291
(36567, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now THAT''S what I''m talkin'' about! Look at this place!\n\nWe''ve even got a pool out back. Little cold, sure, but ya can''t always have a tropical paradise.', 21463), -- 36567
(32796, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ga''nar is coming. Good. We need his forces if we are to press the advantage.$b$bI can only hope his bloodlust has quelled enough for him to listen to reason.', 21463), -- 32796
(33493, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Lokra has always lacked the patience and control of her older sister. She approaches problems head-first, and relies on her raw talents to succeed.$B$BSeeing the way her and Karg look at each other, I am not surprised she chased him all the way to Grom''gar. What surprises me is that they made it back.$B$BAs usual, I expect we have you to thank for that. You continue to honor us with your deeds.', 21463), -- 33493
(33828, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Iron Horde combines the strengths of every clan. We must continue looking for ways to sever those connections if we hope to defeat them.', 21463), -- 33828
(32994, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'See how their machines fail them! There is no better weapon than pure orc muscle!', 21463), -- 32994
(33785, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Karg scoops up a handful of snow and cleans the gore from his axe.>$B$BYou fight well.', 21463), -- 33785
(33826, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nerok and I are the only surviving prisoners, but we cannot leave just yet.', 21463), -- 33826
(32993, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Help me out of these chains. We have work to do.', 21463), -- 32993
(32992, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Lokra''s gaze remains fixed on her dying frost wolf.>$B$BWe had them... We had them, Asha. You were so fast. So beautiful.$B$BI failed you, Asha. I am sorry.', 21463), -- 32992
(32991, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for finding the others. Karg and his captor are one step ahead of us, but they''re limping.', 21463), -- 32991
(33013, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Thunderlord apprentices toil under the watchful eye of Blackrock orcs.$B$BUsing lava pools as natural forges, they craft components for a type of weapon never before seen by the Frostwolves: cannons.>', 21463), -- 33013
(32990, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You''re back! But where is Karg?', 21463), -- 32990
(32989, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$p! They told me you''d be heading this way. You are late to the party! We are just cleaning up now.', 21463), -- 32989
(32795, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Today is a good day.', 21463), -- 32795
(32794, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'For many years I hunted all sorts of prey alongside my father. This hunt shall honor his memory as well as avenge his death at the hands of these traitorous, honorless Thunderlords.', 21463), -- 32794
(32804, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have shown honor to our clan. This act shall be remembered.', 21463), -- 32804
(32792, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hrmph. The burning smell of Thunderlord. This pleases me, $c.', 21463), -- 32792
(32929, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A fine headcount, commander.', 21463), -- 32929
(32791, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Thunderlord think their numbers will save them.$b$bWe will show them that their numbers count for nothing when hunted by a pack of Frostwolves.', 21463), -- 32791
(32783, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So my brother would not dare come himself?', 21463), -- 32783
(33473, 397, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Grim news indeed, $n.$B$BFor saving Wolf Home, I would name you wolf-$g brother:sister;.$B$BNow we must defend Frostfire Ridge from the Thunderlord clan and the Iron Horde.', 21463), -- 33473
(33929, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Shivertail snuggles up to his mother. He is clearly happy to be reunited with most of his pack.', 21463), -- 33929
(33955, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You startle the small pup.', 21463), -- 33955
(33915, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n. I''m sure Orac will think twice before he strays from the pack again.', 21463), -- 33915
(33470, 397, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 0, 'This Iron Tide threatens to sweep over all of Draenor.$B$BThe pool has shown you a possible future. This vision of the Frostwolf clan''s destruction must not be allowed to come to pass.$B$BYou must stop it, $n.', 21463), -- 33470
(33469, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wolf Home is saved, but I sense a stronger enemy just over the horizon.', 21463), -- 33469
(33468, 547, 397, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Durotan''s trust in you is well-placed, $n. You have mine as well.', 21463), -- 33468
(33807, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Frostwolf clan cannot be held like beasts.$B$BYou fight with honor, $n.', 21463), -- 33807
(33450, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done well in this, but do not become proud. This land has dangers far greater than what you have seen here.', 21463), -- 33450
(33412, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Igrimar winces as you show her Durotan''s orders.>$b$bDon''t look at me like that... ungh... I''ve survived worse.', 21463), -- 33412
(33484, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You found Mulverick?\n\nIt shouldn''t be long before those ogres clear out after you defeated their master.', 21463), -- 33484
(33898, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You got the fire in you alright.', 21463), -- 33898
(34732, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, hero, I owe you both my life and my honor. I ask that you allow me to repay this debt by serving under your command.$b$bYou will find that I am a fearsome hunter. I have also mastered the art of riding the rylaks, which few among the Frostwolves can claim.$b$bWill you accept my service?', 21463), -- 34732
(33483, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have my sincere gratitude, $n.', 21463), -- 33483
(33119, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Who are you, outsider? I saw you freeing some of my kin...', 21463), -- 33119
(33657, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have accomplished great things. We could not have captured this citadel without you.', 21463), -- 33657
(33527, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We called you outsider, $r, but you have shown the strength and heart of a Frostwolf.', 21463), -- 33527
(33344, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The ogres appear to be in disarray and many of my people are now free.', 21463), -- 33344
(33622, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Again we meet...', 21463), -- 33622
(33410, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This room shook when the monster fell. Your deeds shall not go unremembered.', 21463), -- 33410
(33408, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Many were killed or wounded on their way here.', 21463), -- 33408
(33546, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Gol''kosh has completed his mission, then.', 21463), -- 33546
(33526, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These are no ordinary enemies, yet you did not show any signs of weakness.', 21463), -- 33526
(33784, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I now understand how you were able to rescue my clan from the clutches of slavery. Such power!', 21463), -- 33784
(34380, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The clan is prepared. It is time for us to advance on Bladespire Citadel!', 21463), -- 34380
(33816, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If you choose to continue to help our clan, the other Shamanstones will sense your closeness to the Frostwolves and might bless you with more gifts.', 21463), -- 33816
(34379, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hope you are finding your land agreeable.', 21463), -- 34379
(34775, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'As additional missions come to my attention I will make them available here.', 21463), -- 34775
(34462, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, commander. Olin spoke to me of your bravery and has already offered to serve under your command.$b$bIf I may advise you in this matter, I would suggest accepting his service. We could make use of a tauren with his skill set in a land like this.', 21463), -- 34462
(34861, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Commander, it is an honor to serve you.', 21463), -- 34861
(34461, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This will be a mighty fine barracks, I think. I am sure Warmaster Zog will complain about how it needs to be bigger, and with more spikes. He likes spikes...', 21463), -- 34461
(34822, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hey... now that is some nice salvage. Say what you will about the Iron Horde, but they got some serious raw materials to work with.', 21463), -- 34822
(34823, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, boss-mon. The Bladespire ogres been pullin'' back their raiding parties. But ya can bet dey be comin'' back, and in larger numbers. The threat from their citadel must be dealt with soon.', 21463), -- 34823
(34824, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yeah, that''s the stuff. Lumber, stone, peons, more peons. It''s like we are building you a stronghold or something.', 21463), -- 34824
(34378, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Right! I think we''ve got this well in hand now. And hardly an explosion to be found!', 21463), -- 34378
(34765, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Little known fact, old gronn grottos make for great farming soil.', 21463), -- 34765
(34592, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nasty beasts they got here on Draenor.', 21463), -- 34592
(34375, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That should be plenty of wood for now.', 21463), -- 34375
(34364, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I''m under orders to obey your orders, commander.', 21463), -- 34364
(34402, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This land should serve our needs well. I leave it to you to decide how to best use it, commander.', 21463), -- 34402
(33815, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I thank you for returning with my people, and I welcome you as an honored guest.', 21463), -- 33815
(33868, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The shaman grins at the harsh, windblown shore.>$b$bWelcome to the home of my people, $n.', 21463); -- 33868
